result.execSummary:
The defendant Vanessa M Graika was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-False Representation <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(d).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

miscConds.notes: No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for her mental or physical needs; be taken as directed and for only as long as deemed medically and reasonably necessary.  Notify doctor(s) of opiate addiction.  No alcohol; urine screens.  No contact with the victim, Jodee C.
Seek and maintain employment.  Be given job and vocational training.  Cognitive thinking intervention counseling.  Parenting classes/counseling.
Pay restitution to Jodee C. in the amount of $4,867.87. Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargeable in bankruptcy.

Pay DNA surcharge, plus all costs, fees and disbursements; pay supervision fees.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargeable in bankruptcy.
